            <h3>What is the purpose of main.hbs?</h3>
            <p>
                The main.hbs file serves as the core template for our website's layout. It defines the structural elements that are consistent across all pages. These include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Header:</strong> Contains the website logo, branding, and navigation.</li>
                <li><strong>Navigation Menu:</strong> Provides links to different sections of the website.</li>
                <li><strong>Footer:</strong> Displays copyright information and additional links.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                By using main.hbs as the base template, we ensure a cohesive design and simplify maintenance.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="question">
            <h3>Explanation of Input Elements in addEmployee.html</h3>
            <p>
                The addEmployee.html file features a form for capturing employee information. Here's a breakdown of the input elements:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>First Name:</strong> Text input field for the employee's first name.</li>
                <li><strong>Last Name:</strong> Text input field for the employee's last name.</li>
                <li><strong>Email:</strong> Text input field for the employee's email address.</li>
                <li><strong>Address:</strong> Text input field for the employee's address.</li>
                <li><strong>Enrollment Status:</strong> Dropdown menu for selecting the employee's status.</li>
                <li><strong>Course ID:</strong> Text input field for specifying the employee's course ID.</li>
            </ul>
